cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it focuses on the security challenges faced by Software Defined Internet of Things (SD-IoT) Networks. It also proposes an AI-based two-stage intrusion detection system that captures network flows and applies AI algorithms to detect attacks intelligently. 

It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with network security and intrusion detection. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes an AI-based intrusion detection system. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of software-defined technology to enhance the efficiency and scalability of IoT applications. 

Finally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as the paper applies machine learning algorithms such as Bat algorithm and Random forest for feature selection and flow classification.
